actual: SELECT SUBSTR(T1.Date, 1, 4) AS Year, SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalConsumption FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.Currency='CZK' GROUP BY Year ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What was the gas consumption peak month for SME customers in 2013?
expected: SELECT SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 5, 2) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND T1.Segment = 'SME' GROUP BY SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 5, 2) ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT strftime('%Y-%m', T2.Date) AS Month, SUM(T2.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth AS T2 INNER JOIN customers AS T1 ON T2.CustomerID=T1.CustomerID WHERE T1.Segment='SME' AND strftime('%Y', T2.Date)='2013' GROUP BY Month ORDER BY TotalConsumption DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the difference in the annual average consumption of the customers with the least amount of consumption paid in CZK for 2013 between SME and LAM, LAM and KAM, and KAM and SME?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) - CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Currency = 'CZK' AND T2.Consumption = ( SELECT MIN(Consumption) FROM yearmonth ) AND T2.Date >= 201301
actual: WITH AnnualConsumption AS ( SELECT C.Segment, SUM(YM.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM customers AS C JOIN yearmonth AS YM ON C.CustomerID=YM.CustomerID WHERE YM.Date BETWEEN 201301 AND 201312 AND C.Currency='CZK' GROUP BY C.CustomerID, C.Segment ), AverageConsumption AS ( SELECT Segment, AVG(TotalConsumption) AS AvgConsumption FROM AnnualConsumption GROUP BY Segment ), ConsumptionDifference AS ( SELECT A1.Segment AS Segment1, A2.Segment AS Segment2, A2.AvgConsumption-A1.AvgConsumption AS ConsumptionDifference FROM AverageConsumption AS A1 JOIN AverageConsumption AS A2 ON (A1.Segment='SME' AND A2.Segment='LAM') OR (A1.Segment='LAM' AND A2.Segment='KAM') OR (A1.Segment='KAM' AND A2.Segment='SME') ) SELECT*FROM ConsumptionDifference;

question: Which of the three segmentsSME, LAM and KAMhas the biggest and lowest percentage increases in consumption paid in EUR between 2012 and 2013?
expected: SELECT CAST((SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0))) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'SME' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)), CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) , CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2013%', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T1.Segment = 'KAM' AND T2.Date LIKE '2012%', T2.Consumption, 0)) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
actual: WITH Consumption2012 AS ( SELECT C.Segment, SUM(YM.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth AS YM INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T ON YM.CustomerID=T.CustomerID INNER JOIN customers AS C ON T.CustomerID=C.CustomerID WHERE YM.Date=201201 OR YM.Date=201202 OR YM.Date=201203 OR YM.Date=201204 OR YM.Date=201205 OR YM.Date=201206 OR YM.Date=201207 OR YM.Date=201208 OR YM.Date=201209 OR YM.Date=201210 OR YM.Date=201211 OR YM.Date=201212 AND C.Currency='EUR' GROUP BY C.Segment ), Consumption2013 AS ( SELECT C.Segment, SUM(YM.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption FROM yearmonth AS YM INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T ON YM.CustomerID=T.CustomerID INNER JOIN customers AS C ON T.CustomerID=C.CustomerID WHERE YM.Date=201301 OR YM.Date=201302 OR YM.Date=201303 OR YM.Date=201304 OR YM.Date=201305 OR YM.Date=201306 OR YM.Date=201307 OR YM.Date=201308 OR YM.Date=201309 OR YM.Date=201310 OR YM.Date=201311 OR YM.Date=201312 AND C.Currency='EUR' GROUP BY C.Segment ) SELECT C12.Segment, ((C13.TotalConsumption-C12.TotalConsumption)/C12.TotalConsumption)*100 AS PercentageIncrease FROM Consumption2012 AS C12 JOIN Consumption2013 AS C13 ON C12.Segment=C13.Segment ORDER BY PercentageIncrease DESC LIMIT 1; SELECT C12.Segment, ((C13.TotalConsumption-C12.TotalConsumption)/C12.TotalConsumption)*100 AS PercentageIncrease FROM Consumption2012 AS C12 JOIN Consumption2013 AS C13 ON C12.Segment=C13.Segment ORDER BY PercentageIncrease ASC LIMIT 1;

expected: SELECT T3.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID INNER JOIN products AS T3 ON T1.ProductID = T3.ProductID WHERE T2.Country = 'CZE'

question: Please list the disparate time of the transactions taken place in the gas stations from chain no. 11.
expected: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Date, T1.Time FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.ChainID = 11
actual: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Time FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.ChainID=11;

question: How many transactions taken place in the gas station in the Czech Republic are with a price of over 1000?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country = 'CZE' AND T1.Price > 1000
actual: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country='Czech Republic' AND T1.Price>1000;

question: Among the transactions made in the gas stations in the Czech Republic, how many of them are taken place after 2012/1/1?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country = 'CZE' AND strftime('%Y', T1.Date) >= 2012
actual: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country='CZE' AND T1.Date>'2012-01-01'

question: What is the average total price of the transactions taken place in gas stations in the Czech Republic?
expected: SELECT AVG(T1.Price) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country = 'CZE'
actual: SELECT AVG(T1.Price*T1.Amount) AS AverageTotalPrice FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T2.Country='CZE';

question: For the customers who paid in the euro, what is their average total price of the transactions?
expected: SELECT AVG(T1.Price) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID INNER JOIN customers AS T3 ON T1.CustomerID = T3.CustomerID WHERE T3.Currency = 'EUR'
actual: SELECT AVG(T1.Price) AS AverageTotalPrice FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.Currency='EUR';

question: Which customer paid the most in 2012/8/25?
expected: SELECT CustomerID FROM transactions_1k WHERE Date = '2012-08-25' GROUP BY CustomerID ORDER BY SUM(Price) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT T1.CustomerID, SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalPaid FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-25' GROUP BY T1.CustomerID ORDER BY TotalPaid DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Which country's gas station had the first paid cusomer in 2012/8/25?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25' ORDER BY T1.Time DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-25' ORDER BY T1.Time ASC LIMIT 1;

question: What kind of currency did the customer paid at 16:25:00 in 2012/8/24?
expected: SELECT T3.Currency FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID INNER JOIN customers AS T3 ON T1.CustomerID = T3.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-24' AND T1.Time = '16:25:00'
actual: SELECT T3.Currency FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T3 ON T1.CustomerID=T3.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-24' AND T1.Time='16:25:00'

question: What segment did the customer have at 2012/8/23 21:20:00?
expected: SELECT T2.Segment FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.date = '2012-08-23' AND T1.time = '21:20:00'
actual: SELECT T2.Segment FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-23' AND T1.Time='21:20:00'

question: How many transactions were paid in EUR in the morning of 2012/8/26?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-26' AND T1.Time < '13:00:00' AND T2.Currency = 'EUR'
actual: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-26' AND T1.Time BETWEEN '00:00:00' AND '12:00:00' AND T2.Currency='EUR'

question: For the earliest customer, what segment did he/she have?
expected: SELECT T2.Segment FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID ORDER BY Date ASC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT Segment FROM customers WHERE CustomerID=(SELECT CustomerID FROM yearmonth ORDER BY Date ASC LIMIT 1)

question: For the deal happened at 2012/8/24 12:42:00, which country was it?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-24' AND T1.Time = '12:42:00'
actual: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-24' AND T1.Time='12:42:00'

question: What was the product name of the transaction happened at 2012/8/23 21:20:00?
expected: SELECT T1.ProductID FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-23' AND T1.Time = '21:20:00'
actual: SELECT T2.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.ProductID=T2.ProductID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-23' AND T1.Time='21:20:00'

question: For the customer who paid 124.05 in 2012/8/24, how much did he/she spend during the January of 2012? And what is the date and expenses exactly?
expected: SELECT T1.CustomerID, T2.Date, T2.Consumption FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-24' AND T1.Price = 124.05 AND T2.Date = '201201'
actual: SELECT T1.Date, SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalSpent FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.CustomerID=(SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-24' AND T1.Price=124.05) AND T1.Date>='2012-01-01' AND T1.Date<'2012-02-01' GROUP BY T1.Date;

question: For all the transactions happened during 8:00-9:00 in 2012/8/26, how many happened in CZE?
expected: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-26' AND T1.Time BETWEEN '08:00:00' AND '09:00:00' AND T2.Country = 'CZE'
actual: SELECT COUNT(T1.TransactionID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-26' AND T1.Time BETWEEN '08:00:00' AND '09:00:00' AND T2.Country='CZE'

question: There's one customer spent 214582.17 in the June of 2013, which currency did he/she use?
expected: SELECT T2.Currency FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '201306' AND T1.Consumption = 214582.17
actual: SELECT T2.Currency FROM yearmonth AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date=201306 AND T1.Consumption=214582.17;

question: Which country was the card owner of No.667467 in?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.CardID = '667467'
actual: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.CardID=667467;

question: What's the nationality of the customer who spent 548.4 in 2012/8/24?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-24' AND T1.Price = 548.4
actual: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-24' AND T1.Price=548.4

question: What is the percentage of the customers who used EUR in 2012/8/25?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T2.Currency = 'EUR', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(T1.CustomerID) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25'
actual: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T2.Currency='EUR', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT)*100/COUNT(DISTINCT T1.CustomerID) AS Percentage_EUR_Customers FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-25';

question: For the customer who paid 634.8 in 2012/8/25, what was the consumption decrease rate from Year 2012 to 2013?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2012', Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2013', Consumption, 0)) AS FLOAT) / SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(Date, 1, 4) = '2012', Consumption, 0)) FROM yearmonth WHERE CustomerID = ( SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.Date = '2012-08-25' AND T1.Price = 634.8 )
actual: SELECT (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4)='2013' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END)-SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4)='2012' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END))/SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(T2.Date, 1, 4)='2012' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate FROM yearmonth AS T2 WHERE T2.CustomerID=(SELECT T1.CustomerID FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.Date='2012-08-25' AND T1.Price=634.8);

question: Which gas station has the highest amount of revenue?
expected: SELECT GasStationID FROM transactions_1k GROUP BY GasStationID ORDER BY SUM(Price) DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT T2.GasStationID, SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalRevenue FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID GROUP BY T2.GasStationID ORDER BY TotalRevenue DESC LIMIT 1;

question: What is the percentage of "premium" against the overall segment in "SVK"?
expected: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(Country = 'SVK' AND Segment = 'Premium', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(GasStationID) FROM gasstations
actual: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T2.Segment='Premium', 1, 0)) AS FLOAT)*100/COUNT(T2.Segment) AS PremiumPercentage FROM gasstations AS T2 WHERE T2.Country='SVK';

question: What is the amount spent by customer "38508" at the gas stations? How much had the customer spent in January 2012?
expected: SELECT SUM(T1.Price) , SUM(IIF(T3.Date = '201201', T1.Price, 0)) FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T3 ON T1.CustomerID = T3.CustomerID WHERE T1.CustomerID = '38508'
actual: SELECT SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalSpent, SUM(IIF(SUBSTRING(T1.Date, 1, 7)='2012-01', T1.Price, 0)) AS January2012Spent FROM transactions_1k AS T1 WHERE T1.CustomerID=38508 AND T1.GasStationID IN (SELECT GasStationID FROM gasstations);

question: Which are the top five best selling products? Please state the full name of them.
expected: SELECT T2.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.ProductID = T2.ProductID ORDER BY T1.Amount DESC LIMIT 5
actual: SELECT T2.Description FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.ProductID=T2.ProductID GROUP BY T1.ProductID ORDER BY SUM(T1.Amount) DESC LIMIT 5;

question: Who is the top spending customer and how much is the average price per single item purchased by this customer? What currency was being used?
expected: SELECT T2.CustomerID, SUM(T2.Price / T2.Amount), T1.Currency FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T2.CustomerID = ( SELECT CustomerID FROM yearmonth ORDER BY Consumption DESC LIMIT 1 ) GROUP BY T2.CustomerID, T1.Currency
actual: SELECT T1.CustomerID, SUM(T1.Price) AS TotalSpent, AVG(T1.Price/T1.Amount) AS AveragePricePerItem, T2.Currency FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID GROUP BY T1.CustomerID, T2.Currency ORDER BY TotalSpent DESC LIMIT 1;

question: Which country had the gas station that sold the most expensive product id No.2 for one unit?
expected: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID = T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.ProductID = 2 ORDER BY T1.Price DESC LIMIT 1
actual: SELECT T2.Country FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN gasstations AS T2 ON T1.GasStationID=T2.GasStationID WHERE T1.ProductID=2 ORDER BY T1.Price DESC LIMIT 1;

question: For all the people who paid more than 29.00 per unit of product id No.5. Give their consumption status in the August of 2012.
expected: SELECT T2.CustomerID, T2.Consumption FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Price / T1.Amount > 29.00 AND T1.ProductID = 5 AND T2.Date = '201208'
actual: SELECT T2.CustomerID, T2.Consumption FROM transactions_1k AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID=T2.CustomerID WHERE T1.Price/T1.Amount>29.00 AND T1.ProductID=5 AND T2.Date=201208;
